UNITED STATES of America, Appellee, v. Rocco DELARMI, Appellant. No. 462. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 29, 1933. M. Michael Edelstein, of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (George S. Tarbell, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
